<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - CAB: 5000, 9100, 9200, 9300, 9400 - REMOVE AND INSTALL -
        WIPER ARM (ROOF MOUNTED ELECTRIC WINDSHIELD WIPERS, AFTER JULY 1992)
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="2">
        <title>WIPER ARM (ROOF MOUNTED ELECTRIC WINDSHIELD WIPERS, AFTER JULY 1992)</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Electric windshield wipers are standard equipment on 5000 Series and 9100, 9200, 9300, and
                        9400 models starting July 1992.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc id="x1600501">
            <title>Remove</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With the windshield wipers off and in the park position, disconnect the washer hose (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1600598">Item 1, Figure 98</hotlnk>) at the washer fitting (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1600598">Item 2, Figure 98</hotlnk>) on the cab roof.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the acorn nut and lockwasher (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1600599">Items 1 and 2, Figure 99</hotlnk>) securing the wiper arm and blade (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1600599">Item 9, Figure 99</hotlnk>) to the knurled driver (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1600599">Item 8, Figure 99</hotlnk>) on the wiper pivot (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1600599">Item 3, Figure 99</hotlnk>). Remove the wiper arm and blade.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>Do not pound on or pry the wiper arm. Use an appropriate puller to remove it.</para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f1600598" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg16/G1600579.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="300"/>
                <caption>Figure 98. Washer Hoses and Fittings</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>A. 1.5 INCHES (38 MM)</callout1>
                    <callout1>1. WASHER HOSE</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. WASHER FITTING</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. WEATHER SEAL</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f1600599" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg16/G1600571.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="300"/>
                <caption>Figure 99. Wiper Arm Assembly</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. ACORN NUT 54 TO 62 IN-LBS. (6 TO 7 NM)</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. LOCKWASHER</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. WIPER PIVOT</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. GASKET WASHER</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. FLAT WASHER</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. HEX NUT 144 TO 180 IN-LBS. (16.2 TO 20.3 NM)</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. WEATHER SEAL</callout1>
                    <callout1>8. KNURLED DRIVER</callout1>
                    <callout1>9. WIPER ARM</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc id="x160051a">
            <title>Install</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position the wiper arm and blade in place at the knurled driver on the wiper pivot.
                    Align the wiper arm and blade so the park position of the blade pivot, the point at which the
                    dimension is measured, is 1.5 inches (38 mm) below the weather seal and push the wiper arm and blade
                    onto the knurled driver.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the lockwasher and acorn nut. Tighten to 54 to 62 in-lbs. (6 to 7 Nm).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the washer hose to the washer fitting on the cab roof.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check operation of the wiper and washer.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
